Privacy Policy for PhotoPasta

1. Introduction

Welcome to PhotoPasta! This Privacy Policy outlines how the PhotoPasta team ("we," "us," or "our") handles your information when you use our software application, PhotoPasta ("the App"). At PhotoPasta, we prioritize your privacy and are committed to ensuring that your personal data remains confidential and secure.

2. Information We Do Not Collect

PhotoPasta is designed to respect your privacy, and we do not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. This includes but is not limited to:

    - Personal Information: We do not collect your name, email address, phone number, or any other personally identifiable information.

    - Location Data: The App does not access your device's GPS or location data.

    - Device Information: We do not collect information about your device, such as its model, operating system, or unique identifiers.

    - Photos and Media: PhotoPasta processes your photos and media files locally on your device without uploading or storing them on our servers.

    - Usage Data: We do not track your interactions with the App or collect usage statistics.

    - Cookies: We do not use cookies or similar tracking technologies.

    - Third-Party Integrations: PhotoPasta does not integrate with third-party services, and we do not share your data with any third parties.

3. How We Use Information

Since we do not collect any personal data, there is no information to use for any purpose.

4. Data Security

We take data security seriously, and PhotoPasta is designed to operate exclusively on your device. We do not have access to your data, and no data is transmitted or stored on our servers. Your photos and media files are processed locally and remain under your control at all times.

5. Children's Privacy

PhotoPasta is not directed at children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect any personal information from children. If you believe that we have unintentionally collected information from a child, please contact us immediately so that we can take appropriate action.

6. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. Any updates will be posted here, and the date of the latest revision will be indicated at the top of the policy.

7. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or PhotoPasta's privacy practices, please contact us [via Github issues](https://github.com/trustmaster/photopasta/issues).

Thank you for using PhotoPasta. We hope you enjoy using our App while knowing that your privacy is our top priority.
